    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nCurrently we are checking this condition for angular filetype detection, \r\n\r\n```lua\r\n    if\r\n      matchregex(\r\n        line,\r\n        [[@\\(if\\|for\\|defer\\|switch\\)\\|\\*\\(ngIf\\|ngFor\\|ngSwitch\\|ngTemplateOutlet\\)\\|ng-template\\|ng-content\\|{{.*}}]]\r\n      )\r\n    then\r\n      return 'htmlangular'\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe problem with this is when this condition fails, even if the html file is a file from an angular repo, file type sets to `html`. so the angular specific syntax highlights doesn't work (the treesitter parser coupled with `htmlangular` filetype).\r\n\r\nis there anything we can do for this issue, like including an `or` case that checking if root_dir contains angular.json?\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- install angular cli - `npm i -g @angular/cli`\r\n- create a new angular project - `ng new test`\r\n- `cd test`\r\n- open neovim in the directory `nvim .`\r\n- open `app.component.html`\r\n- replace the contents with just \r\n  ```html\r\n  <div>Hello world!!</div>\r\n  ```\r\n- reopen the same file\r\n- check filetype -  `:set filetype?`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe filetype should be `htmlangular` instead of `html`\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-465+gc69ea53c9\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\ndon't know\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nubuntu 22.04\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
    "closed_at": "2024-07-20T08:33:09Z",
